title: Remove no-op cancel buttons on simple dialogs.
message:
Remove no-op cancel buttons on simple dialogs.
Ref: https://www.google.com/design/spec/components/dialogs.html#dialogs-simple-dialogs

For dialogs that are caused by DELETE buttons, dialogs should have [Cancel] [Delete] buttons.
For dialogs asking to delete something without the user purposely wanting it, they should have text of "Delete ...?" and [No] [Delete] buttons.

title: Implement a version cache, so we do not load versions repeatedly.
message:
Implement a version cache, so we do not load versions repeatedly.
Cache values are implemented using SoftReferences so it is sometimes too quickly evicted by GC, but I think this is better than using a fixed number of strong references, because we don't want RAM not freed for too long.

If the highlight color is modified (or removed), edit (or delete) the most recent row in the db table, but also remove the old rows if they exist.

title: New bookmark/note/highlight system.
message:
New bookmark/note/highlight system.
Previously, bookmark/note/highlight are tied to ari, so it was
impossible to have multiple bookmark/note/highlight on a same verse.
Now one verse can have multiple bookmarks/notes/highlights.

The model class is Bookmark2 -> Marker
All backup/import/export functions are removed to prevent complications
(Because we’re planning sync. But this might be readded later)

As a side note, KirimFidbek module is also removed. Obsolete.

Still TODO:
- verify edit dialogs are working correctly.
- support showing and triggering edit of multiple
  bookmarks/notes/highlights on a verse.
- support verse count: verse count other than 1 for bookmark and notes
- string label for adding bookmark/notes, must always says “add”

title: Support snappy compression on yes files (initial POC)
message:
Support snappy compression on yes files (initial POC)

Only yes2 files have this support. The attributes entry of the text section of the yes2 file must have these attributes:
- compression.name = "snappy-blocks"
- compression.version = 1
- compression.info = simplemap {
  - block_size = (int) size of one uncompressed block
  - compressed_block_sizes = (int[]) sizes of the compressed blocks
}

title: Revamp rendering of formatted verses.
message:
Revamp rendering of formatted verses.

Previously we used multiple TextViews for each indented paragraph.
That meant we need to destroy and create TextView many times when scrolling.
Moreover, there are two different layout XML files for simple verse
and (formatted/tiled) verse.

Now, tiled and simple verses use the same layout XML.
And the indentation etc uses spans. Also support for paragraph-start
markers with first-line indent and a spacing before.

Also: VerseNumberSpan to make verse numbers smaller, lifted up, and colored
at the same time.

TODO highlight color not applied

message:
Alkitab converter for in-tb-usfm. Now correctly recognizes each type
of paragraph: @0 for non-first-line indented paragraph,
@1 @2 @3 @4 for poems with that indentation level
@^ for first-line indented paragraph.

title: Search field on the top of the search screen is replaced with SearchView for…
message:
Search field on the top of the search screen is replaced with SearchView for Android >= 3.0 (API 11).

dev notes:
Api11_compat class is defined as inner class of Search2Activity. The reason is that we want to prevent the dalvik verifier to be allergic to references to SearchView when loading Search2Activity class.
By defining Api11_compat as inner class, it's considered as a separate class when compiled, and we make it such that Api11_compat is not instantiated at all on runtime when we do not use an API 11 device, so dalvik verifier won't complain anything.

      Alkitab Terjemahan Baru dengan Nomor strong

   Teks Alkitab Terjemahan Baru Indonesia (c) LAI 1974

======================================================================

Perlu kami sampaikan bahwa saat ini penyelesaian modul Alkitab 
Terjemahan Baru dengan nomor Strong masih dalam proses. Untuk itu kami 
mohon pengertian Anda. 


KOREKSI TEKS ALKITAB TERJEMAHAN BARU
====================================
ERRATA I: Koreksi kesalahan pemrosesan teks yang mengakibatkan
          beberapa kata terpotong atau tersambung secara tidak benar.
ERRATA II: Kata-kata yang sengaja diganti karena memuat karakter ASCII
           8 bit yang tidak dapat diolah oleh pemroses teks OLB.
ERRATA III: Perbaikan teks sesuai EYD yang belum dilakukan.
ERRATA IV: Kesalahan-kesalahan lain.

ERRATA I
--------
berlebih-lebihank -> berlebih-lebihankah,
ayat: 1Korintus 9:11

ayat: Hakim 14:17; Ester 2:22
